adjectives.description: tanged (comparative more tanged, superlative most tanged)

entries.meaning: Having a tang (projecting part of an object for securing it).
examples: Sandars identifies two varieties, tanged and tangless. The blades with tangs or short “necks,” where the handles are attached with two rivets, seem to be more common in LM III Crete.

entries.meaning: simple past tense and past participle of tang
